properties.policyContent:
[concat('<!--
    IMPORTANT:
    - Policy elements can appear only within the <inbound>, <outbound>, <backend> section elements.
    - Only the <forward-request> ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' element can appear within the <backend> section element.
    - To apply a ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' to the incoming request (before it is forwarded to the backend service), place a corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' element within the <inbound> section element.
    - To apply a ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' to the outgoing response (before it is sent back to the caller), place a corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' element within the <outbound> section element.
    - To add a ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' position the cursor at the desired insertion point and click on the round button associated with the ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),'.
    - To remove a ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),', delete the corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' statement from the ', parameters('policies_policy_name'),' document.
    - Policies are applied in the order of their appearance, from the top down.
-->
<policies>
  <inbound />
  <backend>
    <forward-request />
  </backend>
  <outbound />
</policies>')]

properties.subject: Your subscription to the $ProdName
properties.body:
Greetings $DevFirstName $DevLastName!

Thank you for subscribing to the $ProdName and welcome to the $OrganizationName developer community. We are delighted to have you as part of the team and are looking forward to the amazing applications you will build using our API!

Below are a few subscription details for your reference:

    #if ($SubStartDate != "")
  • Start date: $SubStartDate
    • #end #if ($SubTerm != "")
  • Subscription term: $SubTerm
    • #end

Visit the developer profile area to manage your subscription and subscription keys

A couple of pointers to help get you started:

Learn about the API

The API documentation provides all information necessary to make a request and to process a response. Code samples are provided per API operation in a variety of languages. Moreover, an interactive console allows making API calls directly from the developer portal without writing any code.

Feature your app in the app gallery

You can publish your application on our gallery for increased visibility to potential new users.

Stay in touch

If you have an issue, a question, a suggestion, a request, or if you just want to tell us something, go to the Issues page on the developer portal and create a new topic.

Happy hacking,

The $OrganizationName API Team

$DevPortalUrl

properties.policyContent:
[concat('<!--
    IMPORTANT:
    - Policy elements can appear only within the <inbound>, <outbound>, <backend> section elements.
    - Only the <forward-request> ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' element can appear within the <backend> section element.
    - To apply a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' to the incoming request (before it is forwarded to the backend service), place a corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' element within the <inbound> section element.
    - To apply a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' to the outgoing response (before it is sent back to the caller), place a corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' element within the <outbound> section element.
    - To add a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' position the cursor at the desired insertion point and click on the round button associated with the ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),'.
    - To remove a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),', delete the corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' statement from the ', parameters('policies_policy_name_1'),' document.
    - Position the <base> element within a section element to inherit all policies from the corresponding section element in the enclosing scope.
    - Remove the <base> element to prevent inheriting policies from the corresponding section element in the enclosing scope.
    - Policies are applied in the order of their appearance, from the top down.
-->
<policies>
  <inbound>
    <base />
    <!--ip-filter action="allow">
            <address>194.19.233.32</address>
            <address>13.91.254.72</address>
            <address>80.232.243.118</address>
        </ip-filter-->
    <!--
This relies on a number of properties being defined in API Management:

	EnableCache  Either true or false. This is used to enable and disable caching of tokens.
	OAuth2TokenEndpoint  The AAD OAuth2 token endpoint URI to get a token from. It takes the form https://login.microsoftonline.com/<subscription-guid>/oauth2/token.
	OAuth2ClientCredentials  The client ID GUID of the AAD application registered for the API Management server to authenticate.
	OAuth2ClientSecret  The client secret key generated for the AAD application registered for the API Management server.
	OAuth2Resource  The application ID URI for the application whose API is being accessed, and who is enabled for delegation in the AAD application registered for the API Management server.

-->
    <choose>
      <when condition="@("{{EnableCache}}" == "true")">
        <cache-lookup-value key="cache_oauth2_access_token" default-value="empty" variable-name="access_token" />
      </when>
      <otherwise>
        <set-variable name="access_token" value="empty" />
      </otherwise>
    </choose>
    <choose>
      <when condition="@(((string)context.Variables["access_token"]) == "empty")">
        <send-request mode="new" response-variable-name="token" timeout="10" ignore-error="false">
          <set-url>{{OAuth2TokenEndpoint}}</set-url>
          <set-method>POST</set-method>
          <set-header name="Content-Type" exists-action="override">
            <value>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</value>
          </set-header>
          <set-body>grant_type=password&client_id={{OAuth2ClientCredentials}}&client_secret={{OAuth2ClientSecret}}&username={{URAuthUsername}}&password={{URAuthPassword}}</set-body>
        </send-request>
        <set-variable name="response" value="@(((IResponse)context.Variables["token"]).Body.As<JObject>())" />
        <set-variable name="access_token" value="@(((JObject)context.Variables["response"]).GetValue("access_token").ToString())" />
        <set-variable name="cache_duration" value="@(int.Parse(((JObject)context.Variables["response"]).GetValue("expires_in").ToString()) / 2)" />
        <cache-store-value key="cache_oauth2_access_token" value="@((string)context.Variables["access_token"])" duration="@((int)context.Variables["cache_duration"])" />
      </when>
    </choose>
    <set-header name="Authorization" exists-action="override">
      <value>@($"Bearer {context.Variables["access_token"]}")</value>
    </set-header>
    <set-header name="Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key" exists-action="delete" />
    <set-backend-service base-url="https://info-test.ur.gov.lv/api/ws" />
  </inbound>
  <backend>
    <base />
  </backend>
  <outbound>
    <base />
  </outbound>
  <on-error>
    <base />
    <trace source="source name">@(context.Request.Url.ToUri().ToString())</trace>
  </on-error>
</policies>')]

[concat('<!--
    IMPORTANT:
    - Policy elements can appear only within the <inbound>, <outbound>, <backend> section elements.
    - To apply a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_5'),' to the incoming request (before it is forwarded to the backend service), place a corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name_5'),' element within the <inbound> section element.
    - To apply a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_5'),' to the outgoing response (before it is sent back to the caller), place a corresponding ', parameters('policies_policy_name_5'),' element within the <outbound> section element.
    - To add a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_5'),', place the cursor at the desired insertion point and select a ', parameters('policies_policy_name_5'),' from the sidebar.
